CAPE TOWN - Cape Town mayor Patricia de Lille says she will hold onto her job until her battle with the DA is over. The party has put talks on her political future on ice. READ: DA executive suspends deliberations on De Lille matter, awaits legal advice The Federal Executive was meant to make an announcement on whether or not it will fire the Cape Town mayor. De Lille says if she’s axed, she’ll serve the party with court papers. Over and above corruption charges and maladministration, the DA is accusing De Lille of bringing the party into disrepute. eNCA